quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  89,25,"So on that Day none will punish as He will punish."
  89,26,"And none will bind (the wicked, disbelievers and polytheists) as He will bind."
  89,27,"(It will be said to the pious believers of Islamic Monotheism): "
  90,19,"But those who disbelieved in Our Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.), they are those on the Left Hand (the dwellers of Hell)."
  90,20,"The Fire will be shut over them (i.e. they will be enveloped by the Fire without any opening or window or outlet.{1}",footnotes:1:[{90:20} "Therein breathing out with deep sighs and roaring will be their portion, and therein they will hear not. **" [The Qur’ân, Verse Verse 21:100]]
  92,13,"And truly, unto Us (belong) the last (Hereafter) and the first (this world)."
  92,14,"Therefore I have warned you of a blazing Fire (Hell)."
  92,15,"None shall enter it save the most wretched."
  93,10,"And repulse not the beggar."
  93,11,"And proclaim the Grace of your Lord (i.e. the Prophethood and all other Graces)."
  94,7,"So when you have finished (your occupation), devote yourself for Allâh’s worship."
  94,8,"And to your Lord (Alone) turn (all your) intentions and hopes."
  95,4,"Verily, We created man in the best stature (mould)."
  95,5,"Then We reduced him to the lowest of the low."
  95,6,"Save those who believe (in Islâmic Monotheism) and do righteous deeds. Then they shall have a reward without end (Paradise)."
  96,1,"Read! In the Name of your Lord Who has created (all that exists)."
  96,2,"He has created man from a clot (a piece of thick coagulated blood)."
  96,3,"Read! And your Lord is the Most Generous."